🔁 What is a while loop in Python?
A while loop is used to repeat a block of code as long as a condition is True.
👉 Simple meaning:
“Jab tak condition true hai, tab tak loop chalta rahega.”

✅ Basic Syntax
while condition:
    # code block
📌 Example 1: Print numbers from 1 to 5
i = 1
while i <= 5:
    print(i)
    i += 1

👉 Explanation:
Start with i = 1
Loop runs while i <= 5
After printing, i increases by 1
Stops when condition becomes False

📌 Example 2: Sum of numbers from 1 to 10
i = 1
total = 0
while i <= 10:
    total += i
    i += 1
print("Sum:", total)
👉 Output: Sum: 55

📌 Example 3: Infinite loop (Important)
while True:
    print("Hello")
👉 This runs forever because condition is always True

🧠 Uses of while loop
When number of iterations is unknown
Example: user input until correct password
Menu-driven programs
ATM system, login system
Condition-based repetition
Run until a value reaches a limit

